nt" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig18e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig19a.jpeg" height="1280" width="945" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig19a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig19b.jpeg" height="1280" width="963" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig19b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig20a.jpeg" height="1280" width="918" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig20a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig20b.jpeg" height="1280" width="917" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig20b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig21a.jpeg" height="1280" width="921" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig21a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig21b.jpeg" height="1280" width="918" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig21b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig22" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig22.jpeg" height="1280" width="920" aria-labelledby="fig22" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 22</span> Fibrosing mediastinitis in a 77-year-old man with a history of right pulmonary artery stenosis and histoplasmosis. Axial multidetector CT angiogram shows marked narrowing of the right and interlobar arteries resulting from a partially calcified soft-tissue mass (arrow), a finding indicative of fibrosing mediastinitis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig22">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig23" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.321105232/asset/images/105232fig23.jpeg" height="1280" width="919" aria-labelledby="fig23" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 23</span> Talcosis in a 30-year-old woman with a history of drug use who presented with adrenal insufficiency and dyspnea at exertion. High-resolution CT image of the lung parenchyma shows areas of diffuse ground-glass atenuation in both lungs with centrilobular nodules (arrow) and paraseptal emphysema (arrowhead), findings indicative of talcosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.321105232&amp;id=fig23">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Rubin LJ. Primary pulmonary hypertension. <em>N Engl J Med</em> 1997;336(2):111–117.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1056/NEJM199701093360207">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/8988890/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Primary+pulmonary+hypertension&amp;author=LJ+Rubin&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=N+Engl+J+Med&amp;pages=111-117&amp;doi=10.1056%2FNEJM199701093360207&amp;pmid=8988890">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Runo JR, Loyd JE. Primary pulmonary hypertension. <em>Lancet</em> 2003;361(9368):1533–1544.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(03)13167-4">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12737878/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-sch